review_blob: 2004 bottle.  Poured an almost inky black brown - 100W bulb didnt penetrate the glass.  Thin rusty head.  Raisins and Dutch cocoa which became more pungent as the chill wore off.  French roast and more cocoa  across the tongue.  The warmth afterwards almost made you think it came from the roasted coffee malts....

My first IPA.  Head came a bit slowly, then lingered.  Even copper tone below teh head.  Light, airy lacing, which was matched in flavor.  Most refreshing, and smooth going down.  Dogfishs own deScription of cedar is very apt.  Matched quite nicely with preztels and BBQ sour cream dip.
